Sentencas: The oxidation resistance of the Fe-Cr alloy backbone structure of metal supported solid oxide fuel cells is significantly improved when infiltrated with gadolinium doped ceria (CGO) particles.
Titulo: Oxidation in ceria infiltrated metal supported SOFCs - A TEM investigation

Sentencas: The mechanism for the improved oxidation behaviour is elucidated using various analytical transmission electron microscopy (TEM) techniques including energy-dispersive X-ray spectroscopy and electron energy-loss spectroscopy of focus ion beamed TEM samples.
Titulo: Oxidation in ceria infiltrated metal supported SOFCs - A TEM investigation

Sentencas: The infiltrated CGO is predominately converted into CeFeO3 after high temperature processing, protecting the alloy.
Titulo: Oxidation in ceria infiltrated metal supported SOFCs - A TEM investigation

Sentencas: A thin layer of Cr-oxide is observed to be sandwiched between the CeFeO3/CGO layers and the Fe-Cr alloy particles.
Titulo: Oxidation in ceria infiltrated metal supported SOFCs - A TEM investigation

Sentencas: Despite the improved oxidation resistance at open circuit voltage, during fuel cell testing accelerated oxidation is observed at the triple phase boundaries.
Titulo: Oxidation in ceria infiltrated metal supported SOFCs - A TEM investigation
